On April 1st, 2014, Silver Standard Resources assumed ownership of the Marigold mine from Goldcorp and Barrick. Goldcorp reports a production of 21,800 ounces attributable to their  66.7% interest in the Marigold mine up to the time of sale, which reflects a total production in the first three months of 2014 of (21,800*(1/0.667)) = 32684 ounces. Silver Standard Resources reports a gold production of 129,615 at 100% ownership for the rest of the year. Therefore, total producton is 32,684 + 129,615 = 162,299
